With effect from 15 March, foreign citizens who are not residents of Ukraine will not be allowed to enter the country. Those already in Ukraine will be permitted to leave.
No flights will operate to Ukraine for two weeks from 17 March. There are a small number of flights available for foreigners wanting to depart. You should check with airlines for details of these.
Measures imposed by some third countries to combat coronavirus include restricting entry of foreign nationals and suspending flight operations in those countries. In some cases, British nationals have been denied boarding for flights to third countries. If you wish to leave Ukraine via a third country, check FCO Travel Advice for other all countries you will visit or transit, and check with your airline.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
